country chained to some ex-Mossad's wrist.</i>

25:10.820 --> 25:15.572
<i>High security. But the guy that runs the
auction decides he's gonna cut costs.</i>

25:15.652 --> 25:18.978
<i>Puts them in a regular old
storage unit right here in town.</i>

25:19.058 --> 25:21.952
<i>I case the place.
There's only one guard on night shift.</i>

25:22.032 --> 25:25.522
<i>Poor bastard humps mail all day for the
post office, so he's out like a light...</i>

25:25.602 --> 25:27.723
<i>...soon as the guy before him takes off.</i>

25:27.803 --> 25:30.793
<i>But I can't for the life of me figure out
what unit these truffles are in.</i>

25:30.873 --> 25:34.897
<i>I get this methed-out Bulgarian hacker,
dresses like Obi-Wan Kenobi...</i>

25:34.977 --> 25:39.435
<i>...to try and check client records for me.
No dice, man. Place is old-school.</i>

25:39.515 --> 25:41.538
<i>Strictly paper files.</i>

25:42.418 --> 25:45.207
<i>I pull a favor with Mr. Clean
and borrow a truck.</i>

25:45.287 --> 25:48.615
<i>I start digging through this place's
trash for billing statements, invoices...</i>

25:48.695 --> 25:52.282
<i>...credit card receipts, anything I can
find to track these things down.</i>

25:52.562 --> 25:54.884
<i>But this place shares an alley
with a Korean fish market...</i>

25:54.964 --> 25:59.309
<i>...and the only thing I'm gonna get out
of these dumpsters is fucking cholera.</i>

25:59.389 --> 26:01.291
<i>I tell the chef I'm throwing in the towel.</i>

26:01.371 --> 26:04.160
<i>I mean, this place is 12 floors,
50 units each.</i>

26:04.240 --> 26:06.396
<i>But he begs me to stay on.</i>

26:06.476 --> 26:09.533
<i>Tells me he's gonna pay me
70 cents on the dollar.</i>

26:10.213 --> 26:14.204
<i>So I do a little research,
find out about this guy in New Jersey.</i>

26:14.284 --> 26:17.940
<i>Crazy South African living in a shack
way out in the Pine Barrens.</i>

26:18.020 --> 26:20.843
<i>Got that disease where he's got
no hair on his body.</i>

26:21.423 --> 26:24.514
- <i>He trains truffle dogs.</i>
- WALKER: <i>Truffle dogs?</i>

26:24.594 --> 26:28.134
Yeah, well, they're better than pigs
because pigs eat the things.

26:28.214 --> 26:31.754
Dogs will just dig them up, as long as
you've got food they like better on standby.

26:31.834 --> 26:33.423
Makes sense.

26:34.103 --> 26:37.113
STACY: <i>Turns out there's only
a handful of real deal ace truffle dogs...</i>

26:37.193 --> 26:39.161
<i>...in the whole fucking country...</i>

26:39.241 --> 26:41.484
<i>...and this guy owns two.</i>

26:41.564 --> 26:45.214
<i>Now, as you know, at the time,
I haven't yet cultivated an appreciation...</i>

26:45.294 --> 26:48.309
<i>...for the canine species, but I'm
looking at this little Jack Russell...</i>

26:48.389 --> 26:50.406
<i>...and I'm thinking,
maybe I can make this work.</i>

26:50.486 --> 26:54.280
<i>Get one of those carrying cases,
like what's-her-name with the sex video?</i>

26:54.360 --> 26:57.002
<i>Sneak him right into the place
and sniff the shit out.</i>

26:57.794 --> 27:00.183
<i>This little bastard must smell
my cat or something...</i>

27:00.263 --> 27:02.151
<i>...because he won't even let me get near him.</i>

27:02.231 --> 27:03.553
That ain't gonna work.

27:03.633 --> 27:06.689
- <i>So I have to take the other one.</i>
- WALKER: <i>Wait, there's another one?</i>

27:06.769 --> 27:09.215
STACY: <i>Yeah, I already told you.
This guy's got two of these things.</i>

27:09.295 --> 27:12.295
<i>Keeps the second one in a big-ass cage
he's got built out back...</i>

27:12.375 --> 27:14.130
<i>...because he says it ain't housebroken yet.</i>

27:14.210 --> 27:17.020
WALKER:
<i>He's got a big-ass cage for a Jack Russell?</i>

27:17.100 --> 27:21.337
- STACY: <i>No, man.</i>
- WALKER: <i>What is it, a hound or something?</i>

27:21.417 --> 27:23.274
STACY: <i>Mm-mm.</i>

27:24.219 --> 27:27.981
<i>Goddamn standard poodle.
Haircut and everything.</i>

27:28.061 --> 27:33.066
<i>We cover nine floors, and old boy is doing
his thing, but he's not getting any hits.</i>

27:33.146 --> 27:35.626
<i>At this point I'm getting nervous,
you know, because the morning crew...</i>

27:35.706 --> 27:38.412
<i>...is gonna relieve Sleeping Beauty
in half an hour...</i>

27:38.492 --> 27:40.823
<i>...and Pom-Poms ain't seeing shit.</i>

27:40.903 --> 27:44.380
<i>And just when I'm starting
to think I got conned...</i>

27:54.816 --> 27:56.806
<i>...it's all there.</i>

27:56.886 --> 27:59.592
<i>The goddamn truffle mother lode.</i>

28:00.922 --> 28:02.613
Come on.

28:02.924 --> 28:05.215
<i>So I give Pom-Poms his reward...</i>

28:05.495 --> 28:08.720
...I start loading these things
out into the hall.

28:10.265 --> 28:12.488
And there's Sleeping Beauty.

28:13.068 --> 28:15.818
<i>I don't know what must've happened to
this guy at the post office that day...</i>

28:15.898 --> 28:19.896
<i>...but the way he's looking at me, I can
just tell he's getting ready to put me down.</i>

28:19.976 --> 28:24.200
I can do a stretch just fine, but the prospect
of getting killed over a bunch of mushrooms?

28:24.280 --> 28:25.835
Truffles.

28:25.915 --> 28:28.531
Whatever. It's not sitting right.

28:28.711 --> 28:30.573
So I start praying to God.

28:31.453 --> 28:33.910
<i>And the damndest thing happens.</i>

28:34.380 --> 28:36.812
<i>I mean, if I'd have pulled two .45s...</i>

28:36.892 --> 28:41.152
<i>...this guy wouldn't have thought twice about
peeling my scalp back right then and there.</i>

28:42.897 --> 28:45.058
<i>But this mailman...</i>

28:45.138 --> 28:47.256
...he sees a dog...

28:47.336 --> 28:49.275
...and he's in the wind.

28:49.905 --> 28:52.528
[LAUGHS] Come on. That's bullshit.

28:52.608 --> 28:54.043
On my life, man.

28:54.123 --> 28:58.935
Took old boy straight to the groomers,
dropped $200 getting his pom-pom fluffed.

28:59.415 --> 29:01.673
Been a dog lover ever since.

29:07.122 --> 29:09.147
What the shit?

29:16.731 --> 29:18.440
WALKER: Fucking kid.

30:40.882 --> 30:42.908
[FLIES BUZZING]

31:03.905 --> 31:05.998
[SIGHS]

31:10.912 --> 31:12.939
[INDISTINCT VOICES]

31:55.290 --> 31:56.882
STACY: Kid!

32:01.796 --> 32:03.321
Kid!

32:07.836 --> 32:08.981
Nothing.

32:20.081 --> 32:21.873
What is it?

32:31.593 --> 32:34.850
OFFICER: Dispatch, this is K-309. Checking
out the municipal storage facility...

32:34.930 --> 32:37.840
- ...Conrad and Gardener.
- DISPATCHER: <i>Copy unit K9.</i>

32:38.600 --> 32:40.125
Oh, fuck.

32:53.981 --> 32:57.406
OFFICER: Got a jimmied door here.
Possible signs of forced entry.

32:57.486 --> 32:59.408
Going to let Charlie have a sniff around.

32:59.488 --> 33:03.513
DISPATCHER: <i>Copy that. I need
an additional unit at Conrad and Berger.</i>

33:03.593 --> 33:05.815
OFFICER: [OVER RADIO]
<i>Dispatch, this is car 210 responding.</i>

33:05.895 --> 33:09.385
<i>I'm about eight blocks from Connie,
on Lerner. I'll head over now.</i>

33:09.465 --> 33:12.924
DISPATCHER:
<i>K-309, car 210 is en route to you now.</i>

33:30.118 --> 33:32.137
He fucked us.

33:33.922 --> 33:35.748
The kid fucked us.

33:53.659 --> 33:56.966
DISPATCHER: <i>Be advised, we are looking
for a late '80s gold-colored Cadillac.</i>

33:57.046 --> 33:59.504
<i>Castillo suspects are armed.</i>

34:10.925 --> 34:12.984
[HUFFING AND PANTING]

34:19.266 --> 34:21.292
[GROWLS]

34:21.636 --> 34:25.187
<i>210 is checking the perimeter now.
Other units, please stand by.</i>

34:25.266 --> 34:27.263
OFFICER: Dispatch, we've got
possible activity in here.

34:27.342 --> 34:29.277
Charlie's all fired up over something.

34:29.358 --> 34:31.436
[GROWLING]

34:35.183 --> 34:36.371
[BARKS]

34:36.451 --> 34:40.342
Easy. Easy, easy, boy.
Easy, easy. Good boy, Charlie.

34:40.422 --> 34:43.312
Good boy. It's okay. Who's a good boy?

34:43.391 --> 34:46.181
You're a good boy. You're good.
[LAUGHS] Hey, good boy.

34:46.262 --> 34:49.918
Good boy, Charlie. Good boy.
Who's a little boy? [LAUGHS]

34:50.309 --> 34:53.324
Good boy, Charlie.
You're a good boy, Charlie.

35:03.044 --> 35:07.136
DISPATCHER: <i>210, we're all clear in there.
Just Charlie chasing his tail again.</i>

35:07.216 --> 35:08.460
Copy that.

35:42.250 --> 35:44.075
[LOUD BANG]

35:45.553 --> 35:47.409
GAGE: Let me in.

35:47.489 --> 35:49.547
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

35:56.497 --> 35:58.220
[KNOCKING PERSISTS]

35:58.300 --> 36:02.484
- STACY: What about the dog?
- It's out here playing Frisbee with me.

36:03.154 --> 36:06.447
The thing was half dead to begin with.
Let me the fuck in.

36:07.075 --> 36:08.731
[OBJECTS CRASH]

36:08.811 --> 36:11.401
Are you rearranging the fucking furniture?

36:12.781 --> 36:17.475
Look, there's a van downstairs
in a loading dock.

36:19.253 --> 36:23.281
I bet you my whole share the key's sitting
right there in the dead guy's fucking pocket.

36:40.608 --> 36:42.867
Okay, let me the fuck in.

36:45.880 --> 36:47.917
You pull that shit again,
you're gonna stay out there.

36:47.997 --> 36:49.628
- Yeah, whatever.
- [DOG BARKS]

36:54.021 --> 36:55.107
- [GROWLING]
- WALKER: Fuck!

36:55.187 --> 36:57.969
Shit. Fuck. Shit.

37:07.302 --> 37:08.991
[GROANS]

37:09.071 --> 37:10.278
Fuck!

37:13.241 --> 37:15.098
Hey! [GRUNTS]

37:15.978 --> 37:18.804
- Oh, fuck. Oh, shit.
- [BARKING]

37:21.382 --> 37:23.007
- [GROWLING]
- Run, man. Go.

37:26.421 --> 37:28.377
[PANTING]

37:28.457 --> 37:29.981
Run!

37:33.261 --> 37:35.286
Fuck. Shit.

37:44.692 --> 37:46.765
[BARKING]

37:52.513 --> 37:55.104
- Kid? You hear me? Look at me.
- You okay?

37:55.184 --> 37:58.357
WALKER: Broke a rib. I'll live.
Help me with the fucking kid.

37:58.437 --> 38:01.410
- STACY: Ah, Christ. Fucking shit.
- WALKER: Hang in there.

38:01.490 --> 38:04.980
We're gonna find something
to make you a tourniquet. Okay?

38:05.060 --> 38:07.148
[BARKS AND GROWLS]

38:08.297 --> 38:10.522
Staunch the flow and clean it up.

38:14.002 --> 38:15.587
[PANTING]

38:15.667 --> 38:17.513
- Fuck!
- WALKER: Fuck!

38:17.593 --> 38:18.970
Come on!

38:20.074 --> 38:22.348
Come on. Jesus.

38:22.428 --> 38:24.068
Shit.

38:28.349 --> 38:30.442
[DISTANT INDISTINCT CHATTER]

38:31.619 --> 38:33.711
[DOG WHINES]

38:41.362 --> 38:43.421
MAN 1: Get the fuck out of here!

38:51.439 --> 38:55.049
MAN 2: I got... I got a bag of marbles
around here... [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

39:20.635 --> 39:22.387
[DOGS BARKING]

39:24.605 --> 39:26.326
[WHINES]

39:46.593 --> 39:48.417
That's your prospect?

39:48.497 --> 39:51.186
- Uh-huh.
- MAN: Ain't nothing but a pup.

39:51.266 --> 39:55.324
- I've been working him.
- MAN: Shit. What line he from?

39:55.404 --> 39:57.258
HANDLER: Scatter-bred.

39:57.738 --> 39:59.494
MAN: All respect due...

39:59.574 --> 40:03.418
...I don't think you want a tot going
40 pounds uphill on the Russian.

40:07.115 --> 40:09.160
Do I look like a yard boy to you?

40:13.454 --> 40:15.841
Take the fucking dog
and put it in the corner.

40:17.158 --> 40:19.031
- Come on, boy.
- [DOG PANTING]

40:25.366 --> 40:27.458
[GROWLING]

40:31.692 --> 40:33.732
[GROWLS AND BARKS]

40:38.933 --> 40:40.972
[PANTING]

40:44.619 --> 40:46.844
[BARKING]

40:55.563 --> 40:57.855
You could call it if it's ugly.

40:58.733 --> 41:00.557
You can't.

41:02.703 --> 41:05.520
- [DOG WHINING]
- [SHUSHING]

41:05.600 --> 41:07.698
[BARKING]

41:09.677 --> 41:11.535
Release your dog.

41:12.280 --> 41:14.339
[DOGS GROWLING AND BARKING]

41:17.518 --> 41:19.610
[BODIES CRASHING, FLESH TEARING]

41:31.599 --> 41:33.856
[GROWLING, FLESH TEARING]

41:34.836 --> 41:37.395
- [DOG WHIMPERS]
- [BODY THUDS]

41:44.078 --> 41:46.303
- Here you go.
- Yeah.

41:47.648 --> 41:49.737
No main cables.

41:49.817 --> 41:51.557
Walker knows a good doctor.

41:51.637 --> 41:55.277
He came up doing cuts for Chuck
Wepner, so he's seen a lot worse.

41:55.357 --> 41:59.415
He'll get you squared away,
as soon as we get the fuck out of here.

41:59.995 --> 42:01.819
Sorry about...

42:03.764 --> 42:05.589
Yeah, well...

42:06.534 --> 42:09.060
...sorry about your face.

42:11.739 --> 42:14.395
Fucking Weeble Wobble, man.

42:14.475 --> 42:17.132
What the fuck's a Weeble Wobble?

42:17.212 --> 42:19.035
It's a toy.

42:21.982 --> 42:24.039
Fucking Weeble Wobble, you know?

42:24.719 --> 42:27.600
Weeble Wobble? Don't fall down?

42:27.922 --> 42:30.372
Like... like a... like a Slinky.

42:33.728 --> 42:35.610
Forget it.

42:40.968 --> 42:42.958
Tournament brackets.

42:43.038 --> 42:44.853
WALKER: Looks like it.

42:49.677 --> 42:51.560
Fucking hell.

42:54.048 --> 42:56.538
What are these? Purses?

42:56.618 --> 42:59.374
WALKER: Note 25, 50, 100, two.

42:59.454 --> 43:01.713
This is chump change.

43:02.073 --> 43:03.956
Look at this guy.

43:07.361 --> 43:09.451
Was he fighting pairs?

43:09.531 --> 43:11.553
Tough motherfucker.

43:11.633 --> 43:13.248
Jesus.

43:21.175 --> 43:23.297
Nobody wins.

43:23.377 --> 43:25.811
WALKER: Jesus fuck, this was last night.

43:26.281 --> 43:28.153
Christ, how long until sundown?

43:28.243 --> 43:31.467
STACY: Call our ride in 50,
then get out that fire escape.

43:32.420 --> 43:34.581
Yeah, well, what say you, kid?

43:37.023 --> 43:38.279
Hmm?

43:38.359 --> 43:42.218
Are you a cat person,
or are you more of a dog person?

43:43.198 --> 43:45.974
Dogs. I used to love them books
when I was little...

43:46.054 --> 43:48.542
...where they got them acting like people.

43:49.504 --> 43:53.061
You know, driving around in cars,
and making deposits at the bank...

43:53.141 --> 43:55.964
...and buying ice cream cones and all that.

43:56.744 --> 44:00.135
Dad kept on having to whup my ass
for trying to talk to them.

44:00.215 --> 44:01.570
To dogs?

44:01.650 --> 44:05.265
I'd see them tied up outside the store,
and I'd ask where they parked their trucks.

44:05.345 --> 44:06.288
[CHUCKLES]

44:06.387 --> 44:10.644
I always wanted one, but Pops
said he could hardly keep us fed. So...

44:10.724 --> 44:14.182
- ...I had chickens and stuff.
- You a farm boy?

44:14.262 --> 44:16.518
No, just... just country.

44:16.598 --> 44:19.955
A few egg hens, a busted-ass old milk cow.

44:21.836 --> 44:25.854
I found this one dog by the side
of the road when I was 6.

44:27.207 --> 44:29.865
It couldn't have been more
than a couple years old.

44:30.645 --> 44:35.097
He must've got hit by a car or something.
His leg was busted up real bad.

44:36.860 --> 44:39.592
He was a... he was a shepherd, I think.

44:47.428 --> 44:48.650
[WHIMPERS]

44:48.730 --> 44:52.621
<i>I knew my pop wouldn't let me keep him.
The dog catcher would just put him down.</i>

44:52.701 --> 44:57.091
<i>So I hauled his poor ass all the way back to
this old shack we had out behind our house.</i>

44:57.171 --> 45:01.062
<i>And Dad was drinking so much by then
I knew the toolshed's the last place he'd be.</i>

45:01.442 --> 45:04.733
<i>But this little dog was crying so loud
from the pain that first day...</i>

45:04.813 --> 45:07.969
<i>...I was sure he'd hear
no matter how loaded he was.</i>

45:08.049 --> 45:10.872
<i>I stayed in there all night, petting him
and begging him to be quiet...</i>

45:10.952 --> 45:13.168
<i>...till he finally calmed down.</i>

45:14.255 --> 45:16.444
<i>Started bringing my lunches home from school.</i>

45:16.524 --> 45:18.980
<i>At first all he wanted
was that cheese you peel off.</i>

45:19.060 --> 45:22.433
<i>But a few days in I had him grubbing on
meatballs, and smiley face tater tots...</i>

45:22.513 --> 45:25.984
<i>...and chicken nuggets, and all that,
like a regular schoolboy.</i>

45:26.714 --> 45:28.537
<i>Had to clean the shit
off his fur every day...</i>

45:28.617 --> 45:32.294
<i>...'cause his leg was still too fucked
to stand up. But I didn't mind.</i>

45:33.124 --> 45:37.266
<i>Nobody'd ever been that happy to see me my
whole life as when I walked in that room.</i>

45:37.346 --> 45:41.664
<i>Tail wagging so hard against the ground
he's kicking up dust all over himself.</i>

45:42.710 --> 45:43.906
[DOOR CHIME DINGS]

45:43.986 --> 45:47.172
<i>I'd hide food under my bed to save up
for the weekends, you know...</i>

45:47.252 --> 45:50.679
<i>...but it was June already.
Pretty soon school was done.</i>

45:50.759 --> 45:54.583
<i>I busted open my piggy bank, sold some
baseball cards I had from Christmas...</i>

45:54.663 --> 45:58.086
<i>and bought him some food,
but I ran out after a week.</i>

45:58.766 --> 46:02.190
<i>Had to swear I wouldn't come back to the
only store after I got caught racking Alpo...</i>

46:02.270 --> 46:04.553
<i>...to convince them not to tell my pop.</i>

46:07.575 --> 46:10.065
<i>Only one place left to go for food.</i>

46:11.145 --> 46:13.602
<i>I was having nightmares
just thinking about it.</i>

46:13.682 --> 46:16.692
<i>But the look on that dog's face
after a couple days...</i>

46:18.152 --> 46:20.575
<i>...it was like not eating
wasn't the worst of it for him.</i>

46:20.655 --> 46:23.960
<i>Like he thought he was in trouble, you know?
Like he thought I was punishing him...</i>

46:24.040 --> 46:27.082
<i>...for something, and he couldn't
figure out what it was he did wrong.</i>

46:27.792 --> 46:31.831
<i>Started to get this froth
around his lips. Tail slowing down.</i>

46:32.211 --> 46:35.265
<i>Two more days,
and it wasn't hardly moving at all.</i>

46:36.270 --> 46:38.616
<i>It got so I couldn't stand it anymore.</i>

46:41.776 --> 46:45.627
<i>Waited till late at night.
Never been so scared in my whole life.</i>

46:46.981 --> 46:50.104
<i>Took a big old block of hamburg
from the fridge.</i>

46:50.184 --> 46:52.544
<i>Buried the wrapper with the chickens.</i>

46:53.154 --> 46:56.405
I can still see that dog's face
when he saw me come in with it.

46:56.485 --> 46:59.581
Swear to God he's grinning at me
just like a little kid.

47:00.261 --> 47:04.679
Tears running down his nose,
because he's crying, he's so happy.

47:06.383 --> 47:09.268
<i>Next morning I came back in from my chores.</i>

47:10.404 --> 47:13.622
<i>Chickens. They must have dug it up.</i>

47:16.126 --> 47:17.967
<i>I was praying while I ran.</i>

47:18.647 --> 47:21.863
<i>Like if I prayed hard enough,
everything was gonna be okay.</i>

47:31.759 --> 47:33.214
<i>My dad...</i>

47:34.394 --> 47:36.411
<i>...he was waiting for me.</i>

47:38.866 --> 47:40.689
Worst part of it was...

47:41.619 --> 47:45.161
...dog's got that same look he
always did when he saw me come in.

47:46.341 --> 47:48.223
Like he's smiling at me.

47:49.643 --> 47:51.714
Tail just wagging away in the dust.

47:56.517 --> 47:58.600
[DOG YELPS]

48:01.422 --> 48:03.386
I was stupid.

48:07.795 --> 48:09.811
[CLEARS THROAT AND SNIFFLES]

48:12.499 --> 48:14.382
Stupid kid.

48:15.753 --> 48:17.636
I'm really tired.

48:31.919 --> 48:33.936
[SOBS SOFTLY]

48:47.734 --> 48:51.360
